====Verb====
{{en-verb}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive|aviation}} To [[turn]] about the [[vertical]] [[axis]] while maintaining [[course]].
# {{lb|en|intransitive|nautical}} To [[swerve]] off course to [[port]] or [[starboard]].
# {{lb|en|intransitive|nautical}} To [[steer]] badly, [[zigzag]]ging back and forth across the [[intended]] [[course]] of a boat; to go out of the line of course.
#* {{RQ:Lowell Fireside Travels }}
#*: Just as he would lay the ship's course, all '''yawing''' being out of the question.
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[rise]] in [[blister]]s, breaking in white [[froth]], as [[cane]] [[juice]] in the [[clarifier]]s in sugar works.
